 Trading activities on the floor of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) yesterday closed downswing, as the overall market performance indices dropped by 0.16 per cent following sell pressure.
Transactions on the stock market had the previous trading session closed on the positive trajectory.
However, at the close of trading yesterday, the All-Share Index dropped by 52.81basis points or 0.16 per cent to close at 31,254.19 index points as against 31,307.00 recorded the previous session, while the market capitalisation of equities depreciated by N23 billion from N13.789 trillion the previous day to N13.766 trillion.
Meanwhile, a turnover of 376.8 million shares exchanged in 4,550 deals was recorded in the day’s trading.
Premium sub-sector was the most active (measured by turnover volume) with 168.5 million shares exchanged by investors in 2,143 deals.
Volume in the sub-sector was largely driven by the activities in the shares of UBA Plc and Zenith Bank Plc.
The banking sub- sector boosted by the activities in the shares of Sterling Bank Plc and Fidelity Bank Plc followed with a turnover of 55 million shares in 527 deals.
The number of gainers at the close of trading session was 20, while decliners closed at 19.
Further analysis of the day’s trading showed that Livestock Feeds Nigeria Plc topped the gainers’ table with 9.26 per cent to close at 59 kobo per share, while Law Union and Rock Insurance Plc followed with 9.09 per cent to close at 48 kobo per share. Sterling Bank Plc tailed with a gain of 8.70 per cent to close at N2.25 per share.
On the flip side, Japaul Oil Plc led the losers’ chart with a drop of 10 per cent to close at 27 kobo per share. Berger Paints Plc trailed with a loss of 9.52 per cent to close at N6.65 per share, while Unilever Nigeria Plc dropped by 8.01 per cent to close at N31.00 per share.